ction", "type": "boolean", "label": "Reduce dimensions in subsampled outputs", "help": "If enabled (default), subsampled outputs are written with a minimal LAS schema (smaller files). The initial source-to-COPC normalization step still preserves all input dimensions.", "help_format": "html", "refresh_on_change": false, "optional": false, "hidden": false, "is_dynamic": false, "value": true, "truevalue": "True", "falsevalue": "False"}, {"model_class": "IntegerToolParameter", "name": "chunk_size", "argument": "--chunk-size", "type": "integer", "label": "Chunk size (points)", "help": "Performance knob. Controls chunked reads used during COPC normalization and later spatial slicing steps.", "help_format": "html", "refresh_on_change": false, "min": 100000, "max": 200000000, "optional": false, "hidden": false, "is_dynamic": false, "value": "20000000", "area": false, "datalist": []}]}, {"model_class": "ConditionalWhen", "value": "filter", "inputs": [{"model_class": "DataToolParameter", "name": "input_segmented", "argument": null, "type": "data", "label": "Segmented tiles (LAZ/LAS)", "help": "One or more segmented tile files (e.g. `output_segmented` from RayCloudTools/SegmentAnyTree). Tip: filenames (element identifiers) should contain `cXX_rYY` so tiles and tree TXT can be matched reliably. Note: do not include mesh `.ply` files here (these inputs are LAZ/LAS only).", "help_format": "html", "refresh_on_change": true, "optional": false, "hidden": false, "is_dynamic": false, "value": null, "extensions": ["laz", "las"], "edam": {"edam_formats": ["format_2333", "format_2333"], "edam_data": ["data_0006", "data_0006"]}, "multiple": true, "min": null, "max": null, "options": {"dce": [], "ldda": [], "hda": [], "hdca": []}, "tag": null}, {"model_class": "DataToolParameter", "name": "input_tree_files", "argument": null, "type": "data", "label": "Tree files (TXT, optional)", "help": "Per-tile tree TXT sidecars (e.g. `output_trees`). If provided, SmartTile will carry them along and (if